HEADWORD: Instauration
<hw>In`stau*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>instauratio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>instauration</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Restoration after decay, lapse, or dilapidation; renewal; repair;
renovation; renaissance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some great catastrophe or . . . <qex>instauration</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>T. Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instaurator</ent>⟦br⟧
